0Neither%20reached%20a%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20all%20charges.%20Regularly%20assailing%20Smith%20as%20%E2%80%9Cderanged%2C%E2%80%9D%20Trump%20depicted%20the%20cases%20as%20politically%20motivated%20attempts%20to%20damage%20his%20campaign%20and%20political%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20two%20former%20co-defendants%20in%20the%20classified%20documents%20case%20sought%20to%20block%20the%20release%20of%20the%20report%2C%20days%20before%20Trump%20is%20set%20to%20return%20to%20office%20on%20Jan.%2020.%20Courts%20rebuffed%20their%20demands%20to%20prevent%20its%20publication%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20District%20Judge%20Aileen%20Cannon%2C%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20documents%20case%2C%20has%20ordered%20the%20Justice%20Department%20for%20now%20to%20halt%20plans%20to%20allow%20certain%20senior%20members%20of%20Congress%20to%20privately%20review%20the%20documents%20section%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20much%20new%20information%20the%20public%20portion%20of%20the%20report%20will%20contain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20gave%20a%20detailed%20view%20of%20their%20case%20against%20Trump%20in%20previous%20court%20filings.%20A%20congressional%20panel%20in%202022%20published%20its%20own%20700-page%20account%20of%20Trump's%20actions%20following%20the%202020%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20investigations%20concluded%20that%20Trump%20spread%20false%20claims%20of%20widespread%20voter%20fraud%20following%20the%202020%20election%2C%20pressured%20state%20lawmakers%20not%20to%20certify%20the%20vote%20and%20ultimately%20sought%20to%20use%20fraudulent%20groups%20of%20electors%20pledged%20to%20vote%20for%20Trump%2C%20in%20states%20actually%20won%20by%20Biden%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20stop%20Congress%20from%20certifying%20Biden's%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20culminated%20in%20the%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%20attack%20on%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%20when%20a%20mob%2