e-she-refused-patch-up-7468972%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gazprom%2C%20Russia's%20energy%20giant%2C%20is%20discussing%20a%2040%25%20cut%20to%20its%20HQ%20staff%20as%20the%20war%20keeps%20Moscow%20cut%20off%20from%20Western%20customers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20speaks%20with%20Gazprom%20CEO%20Alexei%20Miller%20as%20they%20visit%20the%20Lakhta%20Centre%20skyscraper%2C%20the%20headquarters%20of%20Gazprom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6785dbad50dfd88e193e2cc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222021%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20letter%20from%20a%20member%20of%20Gazprom's%20board%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20CEO%20Alexei%20Miller%2C%20pictured%20on%20the%20left%2C%20requesting%20for%20a%2040%25%20cut%20to%20staff%20at%20the%20company's%20St.%20Petersburg%20headquarters.%3Cp%3EALEXANDRE%20ZHOLOBOV%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20state-owned%20gas%20giant%20is%20mulling%20a%20sweeping%20cut%20to%20its%20managing%20staff%20in%20St.%20Petersburg.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20letter%20from%20Gazprom's%20board%20to%20its%20CEO%20suggested%20layoffs%20of%2040%25%20for%20its%20headquarters%20amid%20%26quot%3Bchallenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20letter%20said%20wages%20among%20managers%20had%20risen%20to%20nearly%20%24500%20million%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20energy%20giant%20Gazprom%20is%20considering%20a%2040%25%20cut%20to%20its%20headquarters%20staff%20after%20posting%20its%20first%20loss%20in%2024%20years%2C%20according%20to%20a%20letter%20from%20one%20of%20its%20board%20members%20to%20the%20firm's%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%2C%20first%20reported%20by%20St.%20Petersburg-based%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F47news.ru%2Farticles%2F263385%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E47News%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%2C%20proposed%20that%20the%20central%20office%20head%20count%20be%20reduced%20from%204%2C100%20to%202%2C500%20people.%20It%20was%20dated%20December%2023%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Gazprom%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20the%20letter's%20authenticity%20with%20Agence%20France%20Presse%20and%20the%20state%20media%20outlet%20TASS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20proposal%2C%20Elena%20Ilyukhina%2C%20the%20board's%20deputy%20chairperson%2C%20wrote%20that%20wages%20for%20Gazprom%20managers%20had%20risen%20several%20times%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20to%20about%20%24486.5%20million%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20challenges%20facing%20the%20Gazprom%20group%20require%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20time%20required%20for%20preparing%20and%20taking%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20to%20CEO%20Alexei%20Miller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIlyukhina%20added%20that%20the%20company%20could%20instead%20rely%20on%20%26quot%3Bautomation%20and%20digitalization%26quot%3B%20for%20roles%20like%20accounting%20and%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E47News%20wrote%20that%20Ilyukhina%20also%20estimated%20a%2040%25%20cut%20would%20align%20Gazprom's%20management-to-employee%20ratio%20with%20that%20of%20Rosatom%2C%20a%20state-owned%20nuclear%20energy%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGazprom%20said%20in%20June%202024%20that%20it%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.interfax.ru%2Fbusiness%2F965967%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E498%2C000%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%202023.%20In%20comparison%2C%20Rosatom's%20director%20general%20told%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fkremlin.ru%2Fevents%2Fpresident%2Fnews%2F75322%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20October%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20company%20planned%20to%20have%20about%20400%2C000%20employees%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIlyukhina%20added%20that%20some%20money%20saved%20in%20the%20proposed%20job%20cuts%20could%20be%20diverted%20to%20offering%20new%20performance%20bonuses%20for%20remaining%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGazprom%20Group%2C%20which%20is%20mostly%20owned%20by%20the%20Russian%20state%2C%20posted%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frussia-oil-gas-energy-flows-gazprom-sanctions-ukraine-war-putin-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20annual%20loss%20in%2024%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%20as%20wartime%20Western%20sanctions%20pushed%20its%20European%20customers%20to%20sever%20ties%20with%20Russian%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20announced%20a%20net%20loss%20of%20629%20billion%20rubles%2C%20worth%20about%20%246.84%20billion%20at%20the%20time%2C%20for%20the%20year%202023.%20It%20last%20suffered%20a%20net%20loss%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gas%20producer%20has%20continued%20to%20face%20headwinds%2C%20with%20its%20flagship%20company%20announcing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fgazprom-reports-9-month-loss-32-billion-2024-10-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%243.2%20billion%20loss%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20nine-month%20period%20ending%20in%20September%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20Miller%20has%20approved%20the%20layoffs%20suggested%20by%20Ilyukhina%2C%20and%20TASS%20reported%20that%20the%20company%20declined%20to%20comment%20beyond%20confirming%20that%20the%20letter%20is%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGazprom's%20press%20service%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20for%20years%20been%20a%20major%20supplier%20of%20natural%20gas%20to%20the%20European%20Union%20until%20Moscow's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20prompted%20most%20of%20the%20region%20to%20start%20weaning%20itself%20off%20Russian%20energy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consilium.europa.eu%2Fen%2Finfographics%2Feu-gas-supply%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20transition%